HEADWORD: Chisley
<hw>Chis"ley</hw> <pr>(ch⟦icr⟧z"l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>ceosel</ets> gravel or sand. Cf. <er>Chessom</er>.]</ety>
<def>Having a large admixture of small pebbles or gravel; -- said of a
soil.</def> <rj><au>Gardner.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
